./runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-discuss-point-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:114:  - Reasons: Separates name resolution from file location to avoid layers competing to both name and locate the machine, preserves the invariant that authored declarations select the state-machine name, allows validation and execution to share a pure resolver, and gives deterministic file roots for rhei-local, Panta-inherited, and built-in fallback cases.
